  "title": "A Chip and a Chair Is All You Need",
  "summary": "Aboard the traveling casino cruiser Admiral Piett, hosting a galaxy-spanning weapons convention, Caspian Navy Admiral and physician Lynae Cassius lingers at an upper railing, fascinated by an old-fashioned printed flier, when the masked, armored Malus, known elsewhere as Lorn Rhys, joins her to discuss preparations aboard their ship Revenant. They are approached by Nara Rhen, an earnest, nervous independent holo-journalist looking for an interview, and soon by Malif Tal-Tahn, a jaded former Corporate Sector Authority man who recognizes Lynae from years past. Over drinks the group falls into a wide-ranging, prickly debate about war, peace, the decline of the Imperium and New Republic, and whether prolonged peace breeds stagnation, with Malus bristling dangerously when Nara inadvertently references his cybernetics as a disability. Lynae repeatedly smooths tensions and counsels the overwhelmed Nara on respecting subjects, courting sponsors, and presenting timely information to her audience. The conversation ends civilly: Malus accepts Nara's apology and agrees to continue talking philosophy with Malif privately on Athaniss, Nara departs grateful for the unexpected mentorship, and Malus takes his leave with a quiet compliment to Lynae and a reminder to inspect the ship.",
